node.text: “My work centers Black joy, community, and love. I hope that it makes others feel seen, held, and welcome in all their complexities,” says Chiomma Hall of @chiommani. Watch to learn more about how her beautiful prints draw from the intersections of her identity to portray BIPOC and LGBTQIA+ communities reveling in rest, choosing self-care, and communing with loved ones. Then visit her Etsy shop to admire her art: etsy.me/chiommani

Have you voted for your favorite Etsy Design Awards finalist to win the @klarna People’s Pick Award yet? Through 7/20, you can vote by either:⁣
- Favoriting the item on Etsy.com or the Etsy app (head to our link in bio to get started)⁣
- Giving the item an extra vote in the Klarna app, within the Etsy Design Awards Collection (US and Germany only)⁣
⁣
The finalist with the most votes on Etsy and Klarna combined will be named the People’s Pick Award winner and will get $5,000. As a bonus, US shoppers using Klarna will also receive a $10 Etsy credit when they purchase an item from a finalist’s shop during the voting period!
